{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"IMPLEMENTATION NOTE (residual plan-review finding, accepted as build-time detail): after 5 remediation rounds, the plan-review gate's remaining S4b finding is an ever-deeper regress of the exact `review_code()` invocation (diff_text -> repo_root/resolve_gate_handle -> how the shallow checkout at the change ref is fetched). These are build-time integration details to settle by reading `src/rebar/llm/code_review.py`'s actual signature during implementation, not plan-level decisions — and b744-WS6 replaces this minimal review path with the four-pass code-review gate entirely. The deliverable is fixed: the receiver fetches the change at its ref from Gerrit, runs a code review (proven pipe: review_code with a valid repo context; b744: produce_code_review_verdict), maps the result to the LLM-Review vote (PASS->MAX, BLOCK/error->-1 fail-closed) via the stable code_review_decision adapter. The completion verifier will enforce correctness when S4b is built."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782718070331304001,"uuid":"ca572f8f-df88-4d40-8d74-88383afe3393"}